I was there and i read all that with a lot of emotions. As a woman i felt that now someone try to tell the truth. He shows how many mens abuse there power and actually it seems we wanna live in a cloud. This really happen every single day to us! I do not know if the pictures of that what happened to this womens already out there. It seems you can show every womens face there, because it happens right now. I am so sorry, he had to ask them right. Otherwise we HAVE to talk about that. Thanks to the artist. You try to open the eyes of everybody🏆🏆🏆❤️

Art Basel’s Unlimited section opens today and it includes Andrea Bowers’ installation ‘Open Secret’ (2018/2019). The work documents the development of the #MeToo and Time’s Up movements against sexual harassment and assault. ‘Open Secret’ is composed of two long walls that gather a series of banners chronicling the name, profession, employment status, summary of allegations, apology status, and course of legal action taken against a wide array of accused individuals exposed through the rampant attention that these movements brought to the suppression of such violations. Wheeled office chairs are positioned before the walls, allowing viewers to sit and spend more time reading through the exhaustive database compiled by Andrea Bowers’ studio. As Art Unlimited curator Gianni Jetzer has commented, Bowers’ work is a “stunning artistic monument to one of the most important women’s movements globally”. @artbasel @radicalhospitality @giannijetzer #artbasel #artbasel2019 #artunlimited #andreabowers #radicalhospitality #opensecret #metoo #timesup #giannijetzer #kaufmannrepetto #milano #newyork

#GotConsent?#JustSayNoToVictimisingVictims #DoTheRightThing

Sexual assault survivors are not “readymades” to be used and consumed by whatever “artist” (female or otherwise) that chooses to appropriate their lives to make a “statement.” However initially intended and misguided in execution, this “work” has been demonstrably horrific for the survivor, whose beaten body was put on display without her consultation or consent. How is exploiting the abuse and trauma of survivors justified by calling it "art"? Remove the whole installation and stop promoting it on Instagram for likes. The galleries, curator, and art fair “standing by” Andrea Bowers’s work and not the survivors she retraumatized, are not only complicit, but actively providing credibility for the violation in their willingness to sell a woman’s rape for “conversation” and $300,000. #copyrightlawsuit #andreabowers @whatanartshole @andrewkrepsgallery @capitainpetzel  @vielmetter http://www.artnews.com/2019/06/12/art-basel-andrea-bowers-photos-removed/
Disgusting. Take this shit down
